## PRODUCTION SITE — zavis.ai

Every push to `main` deploys directly to production. There is NO staging.

### Before pushing ANY code:
1. Run `npm run lint` — fix ALL errors (unused imports, unused vars, type errors)
2. Run `npm run build` if you added/changed pages
3. Unused imports WILL crash production. Remove them.

### Database:
- Uses `pg` (node-postgres), NOT `@neondatabase/serverless`
- Connection: `import { db } from "@/lib/db"` for Drizzle ORM
- For raw SQL: `import { Pool } from "pg"`
- NEVER import from `@neondatabase/serverless`

### Deployment:
- Push to `main` → GitHub Actions lint check → SSH deploy to EC2
- All scripts run ON EC2 (DB is localhost), not GitHub runners
- `.env.local` is on EC2 only, not in git
- Nginx serves `_next/static` from disk (do not change)

